The paper deals with the wait-free read-write memory model, which is a fundamental topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). It also involves the use of consensus objects, which are commonly studied in the context of distributed systems and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper presents an affine task, which is a concept from algebraic topology and combinatorics (cs.LO). The use of immediate snapshot tasks and the characterization of models equipped with abstractions other than read-write memory involve information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control theory (cs.SY).
